{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784112160302,"sessionID":"ses_09ab2e013ffeLqGUbzFxJIGIMd","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"S7PYXUZ7mwmxLlKN5dS5YUJAfppv7EMi","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Find field rename pattern","prompt":"Search the codebase for examples of struct field renames or similar refactoring patterns to understand how to properly rename struct fields. Look for any documentation or examples in the codebase that show how to rename struct fields, or check if there are any comments or TODOs related to field renaming.","subagent_type":"general"},"output":"task_id: ses_09aa42641ffeISfQlKEQcRCtgB (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\n## Struct Field Rename Pattern in Boundary\n\nBased on my search of the codebase, here's how boundary handles struct field renames:\n\n### 1. **Field Name Constants**\nField names are defined as constants in dedicated files to ensure consistency:\n\n```go\n// internal/credential/vault/fields.go\nconst (\n    nameField        = \"Name\"\n    descriptionField = \"Description\"\n    vaultPathField   = \"VaultPath\"\n    httpMethodField  = \"HttpMethod\"\n    // ... more fields\n)\n```\n\n### 2. **Field Mask Validation**\nField masks are validated using `strings.EqualFold` with the constants:\n\n```go\n// internal/credential/vault/repository_credential_library.go\nfor _, f := range fieldMaskPaths {\n    switch {\n    case strings.EqualFold(nameField, f):\n    case strings.EqualFold(descriptionField, f):\n    case strings.EqualFold(vaultPathField, f):\n    default:\n        return nil, db.NoRowsAffected, errors.New(ctx, errors.InvalidFieldMask, op, f)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 3. **Update Path Construction**\nThey use `dbcommon.BuildUpdatePaths` to construct the actual update query:\n\n```go\ndbMask, nullFields = dbcommon.BuildUpdatePaths(\n    map[string]interface{}{\n        \"Name\":                   target.Name,\n        \"Description\":            target.Description,\n        \"DefaultPort\":            target.DefaultPort,\n        \"SessionMaxSeconds\":      target.SessionMaxSeconds,\n        \"SessionConnectionLimit\": target.SessionConnectionLimit,\n        \"WorkerFilter\":           target.WorkerFilter,\n    },\n    fieldMaskPaths,\n    []string{\"SessionMaxSeconds\", \"SessionConnectionLimit\"},\n)\n```\n\n### 4. **Comprehensive Documentation**\nThere's a detailed guide at `internal/adding-a-new-field-readme.md` that outlines the full process for adding new fields to existing APIs, including:\n- Schema changes and migrations\n- Protobuf updates (both storage and API)\n- Repository extensions\n- Handler updates\n- CLI integration\n\n### Key Recommendations for Field Renames:\n1. Define field names as constants in a dedicated `fields.go` file\n2. Use `strings.EqualFold` for case-insensitive validation\n3. Use `dbcommon.BuildUpdatePaths` for constructing update queries\n4. Keep field names consistent between the API, storage, and database layers\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_09aa42641ffeISfQlKEQcRCtgB","model":{"modelID":"unsloth/GLM-4.7-Flash-GGUF:UD-Q4_K_XL","providerID":"local"},"truncated":false},"title":"Find field rename pattern","time":{"start":1784111946187,"end":1784112160301}},"id":"prt_f655bce540013jt6vY9Dady5tt","sessionID":"ses_09ab2e013ffeLqGUbzFxJIGIMd","messageID":"msg_f655b8669001haRu0sS38ON2d2"}}
